1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,175
Experts typically approach data cleaning by following a three-step process.

2
00:00:05,175 --> 00:00:07,365
Before kick-starting this process,

3
00:00:07,365 --> 00:00:10,905
it's critical to make a copy of your original dataset.

4
00:00:10,905 --> 00:00:14,970
All of the cleaning operations are typically conducted on the copy,

5
00:00:14,970 --> 00:00:19,140
so you can still view the original dirty and/or messy dataset later.

6
00:00:19,140 --> 00:00:21,270
If you're working with DataFrames and Pandas,

7
00:00:21,270 --> 00:00:23,295
you can do this by using the copy method

8
00:00:23,295 --> 00:00:25,575
on your dataframe and assigning it to a variable,

9
00:00:25,575 --> 00:00:28,230
for example, in this case, df_clean.

10
00:00:28,230 --> 00:00:32,835
The next step is the definition where we define a data cleaning plan.

11
00:00:32,835 --> 00:00:35,220
We do this by converting our assessments into

12
00:00:35,220 --> 00:00:37,920
cleaning tasks by writing little how-to guides.

13
00:00:37,920 --> 00:00:42,450
This plan also serves as documentation so that your work can be reproduced.

14
00:00:42,450 --> 00:00:47,855
For example, a cleaning task can be removing unnecessary hyphens and variables.

15
00:00:47,855 --> 00:00:52,225
Then we'll actually implement these actions into code and run them.

16
00:00:52,225 --> 00:00:55,040
Finally, you'll test your dataset visually and

17
00:00:55,040 --> 00:00:57,575
programmatically to make sure you're cleaning code worked.

18
00:00:57,575 --> 00:01:00,650
For example, you may inspect the first few rows of the DataFrame

19
00:01:00,650 --> 00:01:04,100
using the dot head method to confirm the hyphens are removed.

20
00:01:04,100 --> 00:01:06,800
In this step, we often revisit assessment to

21
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:09,985
compare the results before and after cleaning.

22
00:01:09,985 --> 00:01:14,195
Programmatic cleaning is referring to using code or automated scripts in

23
00:01:14,195 --> 00:01:18,565
order to clean your data and it's actually preferred over manual cleaning,

24
00:01:18,565 --> 00:01:22,180
so let's look at a couple of differences between these two methods.

25
00:01:22,180 --> 00:01:23,945
When you manually clean data,

26
00:01:23,945 --> 00:01:26,990
you might typically be retyping data or copying and

27
00:01:26,990 --> 00:01:30,410
pasting columns and rows to correct the issues by hand.

28
00:01:30,410 --> 00:01:35,585
This type of cleaning is inefficient and as datasets grow larger and more complex,

29
00:01:35,585 --> 00:01:39,820
it becomes increasingly challenging to maintain data quality manually.

30
00:01:39,820 --> 00:01:41,625
It's also error-prone.

31
00:01:41,625 --> 00:01:44,360
You might accidentally miss some incorrect values or

32
00:01:44,360 --> 00:01:47,765
introduce new errors while typing or copying data.

33
00:01:47,765 --> 00:01:52,370
On the other hand, programmatic data cleaning uses code to fix data quality issues.

34
00:01:52,370 --> 00:01:55,160
It allows work faster and more efficient handling of

35
00:01:55,160 --> 00:02:00,215
large datasets as the cleaning process can be automated and performed on a massive scale.

36
00:02:00,215 --> 00:02:03,365
It also involves using code or scripts to clean the data,

37
00:02:03,365 --> 00:02:06,140
which ensures a consistent approach and reduces

38
00:02:06,140 --> 00:02:09,320
the risk of human error which can occur during manual cleaning.

39
00:02:09,320 --> 00:02:13,805
This consistency leads to more reliable and accurate results in the analysis.

40
00:02:13,805 --> 00:02:17,630
Programmatic cleaning also enables you to create reusable scripts or

41
00:02:17,630 --> 00:02:22,510
functions that can be applied to similar datasets or future data cleaning tasks.

42
00:02:22,510 --> 00:02:26,420
This makes the process more transparent and allows other researchers or

43
00:02:26,420 --> 00:02:30,580
team members to reproduce the cleaning steps and validate the results.

44
00:02:30,580 --> 00:02:34,910
Data wrangling is taking a tremendous amount of time for data professionals,

45
00:02:34,910 --> 00:02:39,930
so programmatic data cleaning is strongly preferred compared to the manual process.

